<headline>Rip Current Statement issued August 08 at 3:44AM CDT until August 08 at 1:00PM CDT by NWS Houston - Galveston</headline>
<description>...HIGH RIP CURRENT RISK REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 1 PM CDT THIS
AFTERNOON...
* WHAT...Dangerous rip currents.
* WHERE...Matagorda Islands, Brazoria Islands, Galveston Island
and Bolivar Peninsula Counties.
* WHEN...Through Tuesday afternoon.
* IMPACTS...Rip currents can sweep even the best swimmers away
from shore into deeper water.</description>
<instruction>Swim near a lifeguard and away from rocks, jetties and piers. If
caught in a rip current, relax and float. Don`t swim against the
current. If able, swim in a direction following the shoreline.
If unable to escape, face the shore and call or wave for help.</instruction>
